datacenter.zeitreihen
Class TimeserieWrapper

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--datacenter.zeitreihen.TimeserieWrapper
public class TimeserieWrapper
extends java.lang.Object

wraps all kind of timeseries that can be owned by a channel or a computation. Channels own work, original, and computed timeseries. NOTE: TimeserieWrapper are not stored as is into the database, they just represent some common business logic upon timeseries.

See Also:
Channel, Computation

ImportFromFile

public int ImportFromFile(java.lang.String filename,
                          java.sql.Date from,
                          java.sql.Date to,
                          boolean bReplace,
                          java.lang.String status,
                          java.lang.String separator,
                          java.lang.String dateFormatPattern,
                          boolean bFast)
imports timeseries from the given file into table owned by this wrapper

Parameters:
filename - pathname of the file to import
from - date from which to import (if null import from beginning)
to - date to which to import (if null import until end)
bReplace - boolean specifying how to handle duplicates (if true, existing values will be replaced by imported ones)
status - status flag that will be used for the flag column (if null uses the imported one)
separator - date, value, flag tokens separator (if null assumes it is the comma character)
bFast - (NOTE: not supported yet, set it to ALWAYS to false) performs a fast import if true. Uses openroad application server
Returns:
the amount of imported rows, if some error occurs it returns -1.
See Also:
SimpleDateFormat

ExportToFile

public int ExportToFile(java.lang.String filename,
                        java.sql.Date from,
                        java.sql.Date to,
                        java.lang.String separator,
                        java.lang.String dateFormatPattern,
                        boolean bFast)
exports the timeserie owned by this wrapper to a file

Parameters:
filename - pathname of the file to create
from - date from which to export (if null export from beginning)
to - date up to export (if null export until end)
separator - string representing the separator between the tokens: date, value, and flag. (if null default is comma)
dateFormatPattern - string such as in SimpleDateFormat representing the format of the date. (if null uses the locale default)
bFast - (NOTE: not supported yet, set it ALWAYS to false) performs a fast export if set to true. For this, uses openroad application server.
Returns:
amount of lines written if successfull, otherwise -1
